{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-13252].
  {panel}

A user reported to me that the instance I am an administrator of no longer shows the "Bulk Edit" menu item when multi-selecting Issues from the Backlog.

I've never personally used the feature, but I do see in this blog post: http://blogs.atlassian.com/2013/08/jira-agile-tip-of-the-month-bulk-changes/ what they described as their expectation of it.

They (and I obviously) do have the global "Bulk Edit" permission and can still do so from the *search screen*, but the option does not show up as described in that blog post. This was all of a sudden, probably related to the February 15th update.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-13226].
  {panel}

I enabled the new Labs Feature "Kanban Backlog". As soon as I enabled it and mapped the status "Backlog" to the boards pseudo-column "Backlog" issues for some users are displayed spanning all columns (Attachment "Span-Without-Filter").

I found a workaround that involved creating a custom quick filter (Attachment "Quick-Filter") explicitly hiding issues with status "Backlog". Applying the quick filter to the board, the issues now display correctly (Attachment "No-Span-With-Filter") but it would be nice to know why it happened in the first place.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-13041].
  {panel}

In Jira Cloud, Agile Board, planning view, the labels for Remaining and Estimate appear at the bottom of an unstarted sprint, along with a forward slash divider, but the numbers are not displayed.  At the same time, if I click on the ... next to user icons at the top of the current sprint no Original Time Estimate is displayed in the column, although there are such estimates.

h3. Problem Definition
As an Administrator I want to make 'Days in column' set to false by default for new Kanban boards 
If you don't use '_Days in column_' functionality, disabling it will speed-up board load. For large instance is not possible to educate all users to disable it. 

h3. Suggested Solution
Make a setting in a Agile configuration to make 'Days in column' set to false by default for new Kanban boards. 

h3. Workaround 
Create a script which polls newly created boards and disable 'Days in column'.
This is *private* API for this, there is no guaranty that it will not change in the future.
* Get list of All boards: {{/rest/greenhopper/1.0/rapidview}}
{code}
curl -v 'http://127.0.0.1:8080/rest/greenhopper/1.0/rapidview' -X GET -H 'Content-Type: application/json; charset=UTF-8' -u admin:pass'
{code}

* Get config of the board: {{/rest/greenhopper/1.0/rapidview/ID}}
{code:borderStyle=solid}
curl -v -X GET -H 'Content-Type: application/json; charset=UTF-8' -u admin:pass  http://127.0.0.1:8080/rest/greenhopper/1.0/rapidview/242

{"id":242,"name":"Some cool name","canEdit":true,"sprintSupportEnabled":false,"showDaysInColumn":false}
{code}

* Modify showDaysInColumn: {{/rest/greenhopper/1.0/rapidviewconfig/showDaysInColumn}}
{code:borderStyle=solid}
curl 'http://127.0.0.1:8080/rest/greenhopper/1.0/rapidviewconfig/showDaysInColumn' -X PUT -H 'Content-Type: application/json; charset=UTF-8' -u admin:pass --data '{"rapidViewId":242,"showDaysInColumn":false}'
{code}
